                        structure: "Lipid A (toxic moiety, anchors LPS in membrane) + Core polysaccharide + O-antigen (outer chain)",
                        mechanism: "Lipid A binds CD14/TLR4/MD-2 complex on macrophages → NF-κB activation → massive cytokine release (TNF-α, IL-1β, IL-6) → fever, vasodilation, septic shock",
                        effects: ["Fever (pyrogen)", "Hypotension and shock", "DIC (disseminated intravascular coagulation)", "Complement activation"],
