                    "3. Glycolysis proceeds in the cytoplasm: Glucose → Pyruvate + 2 ATP + 2 NADH",
                    "4. To regenerate NAD⁺ (required for step 6 of glycolysis to continue), pyruvate must be reduced",
                    "5. LDH: Pyruvate + NADH → Lactate + NAD⁺",
                    "6. All cellular ATP comes from glycolysis; all NAD⁺ regeneration from LDH",
                    "7. RBCs are obligate lactic acid fermenters — oxygen is irrelevant to their metabolism"
