                    "2. Impaired clearance of apoptotic cells → nuclear material (dsDNA, histones) accumulates",
                    "3. Autoreactive B cells (escaping tolerance) produce anti-dsDNA IgG antibodies",
                    "4. Anti-dsDNA binds circulating DNA → immune complex (IC) formation",
                    "5. IC deposits in glomerular basement membrane (type III hypersensitivity)",
                    "6. IC activates complement cascade → C3a, C5a → neutrophil/macrophage recruitment",
                    "7. Neutrophil proteases and ROS damage glomerular basement membrane → proteinuria",
                    "8. Classification: ISN/RPS Class III/IV (proliferative lupus nephritis) most likely"
