                    "2. In buffet setting, B. cereus spores survive cooking of rice → on cooling, germinate → produce heat-stable emetic toxin",
                    "3. Reheating does not destroy preformed heat-stable toxin",
                    "4. Toxin ingested → binds 5-HT₃ receptors in gut → stimulates vagal afferents → emesis/diarrhoea",
                    "5. Staphylococcal enterotoxin (if from handling): superantigen-like gut effects → rapid onset N&V 1–6 hours",
                    "6. Management: supportive (fluids, antiemetics); antibiotics NOT needed — toxin-mediated"
