                                mechanism: "Ants aggressively defend Acacia against herbivores and competing plants; Acacia provides hollow thorns for nesting and nutrient-rich food bodies (Beltian bodies)",
                                study: "Classic experiment by Daniel Janzen (1966) — removing ants from Acacias dramatically reduced growth"
