            "Boreal forests and tundra peatlands together store ~30–40% of terrestrial carbon — highly sensitive to warming",
            "Deserts have the lowest NPP; wetlands and estuaries have NPP rivalling tropical forests",
            "Mediterranean shrublands cover only 2% of Earth's surface but contain ~20% of plant species",
            "Coral reefs support ~25% of marine species despite covering less than 0.1% of ocean floor",
            "Climate change is shifting biome boundaries poleward and upslope, with major biodiversity and carbon consequences",
