                    "1. Bulliform cells on the upper leaf surface lose turgor in dry conditions → leaf rolls inward",
                    "2. Rolling encloses a humid microenvironment around the stomata (located in grooves on upper surface)",
                    "3. Water vapour concentration gradient between leaf interior and enclosed air is reduced",
                    "4. Less diffusion gradient → less transpiration water loss",
                    "5. Also: stomata in grooves trap boundary layer of humid air even when unrolled"
